#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:1
msgid "Operaton Access Patterns"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:3
msgid ""
"This page documents the three distinct ways to access Operaton within the "
"RONL ecosystem. Each pattern targets a different caller, speaks a different "
"protocol contract, and requires a different authentication strategy. "
"Choosing the wrong pattern is the most common source of integration errors."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:7
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:8
msgid ""
"┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n"
"│                         Callers                                 │\n"
"├──────────────────┬──────────────────────┬───────────────────────┤\n"
"│  Human operator  │   AI agent / tool    │  Caseworker portal /  │\n"
"│  (browser)       │   (operaton-mcp)     │  automation script    │\n"
"├──────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────┤\n"
"│  Pattern 1       │  Pattern 2           │  Pattern 3            │\n"
"│  Cockpit         │  engine-rest + OIDC  │  RONL M2M routes      │\n"
"│  (web UI)        │  (native REST)       │  (/v1/m2m/*)          │\n"
"├──────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────┤\n"
"│  operaton-doc    │  operaton-doc        │  RONL Business API    │\n"
"│  directly        │  directly            │  → operaton-doc       │\n"
"└──────────────────┴──────────────────────┴───────────────────────┘"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:24
msgid ""
"The key insight: Patterns 1 and 2 talk **directly to Operaton**. Pattern 3 "
"talks to the **RONL Business API**, which in turn proxies to Operaton. These "
"are not interchangeable — the path structures, authentication mechanisms, "
"and response shapes are all different."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:28
msgid "Pattern 1 — Cockpit (browser)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:30
msgid ""
"The Operaton Cockpit is the built-in web UI for process operators. It is "
"served directly by the Operaton container at the root path and uses "
"Operaton's own session-based authentication."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:32
msgid "**URL:** `https://operaton-doc.open-regels.nl/`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:34
msgid ""
"**Authentication:** Operaton internal user credentials (username/password "
"form login). On the `operaton-doc` instance, the JWT security filter chain "
"only protects `/engine-rest/**` — all other paths including the Cockpit, "
"Tasklist, and Welcome page are permitted without a Bearer token, relying on "
"Operaton's own `LazySecurityFilter`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:36
msgid ""
"**Use for:** Manual process inspection, deployment management, incident "
"resolution, monitoring running instances, viewing the DMN decision tables."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:38
msgid ""
"**Not for:** Programmatic access. The Cockpit has no stable API contract for "
"external callers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:42
msgid "Pattern 2 — `operaton-mcp` via `engine-rest` + OIDC"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:44
msgid ""
"`operaton-mcp` is an MCP server that exposes the full Operaton REST API "
"surface (300+ operations) as AI-callable tools. It talks **directly to "
"Operaton's `engine-rest` API** — bypassing the RONL Business API entirely."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:46
msgid "**Base URL:** `https://operaton-doc.open-regels.nl/engine-rest`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:48
msgid ""
"**Authentication:** OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials via the `operaton-mcp-"
"client` Keycloak client. `operaton-mcp` fetches a Bearer token from Keycloak "
"and attaches it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every request to "
"`engine-rest`. Operaton validates the token via the JWKS endpoint of the "
"`ronl` realm (configured via `spring.security.oauth2.resourceserver.jwt.jwk-"
"set-uri` in `default.yml`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:50
msgid ""
"**Path contract:** Native Operaton `engine-rest` paths — `/task`, `/process-"
"instance`, `/process-definition`, `/history/process-instance`, `/decision-"
"definition/key/:key/evaluate`, `/deployment`, etc. These are exactly what "
"the [Operaton REST API spec]{1} documents."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:52
msgid "**Configuration:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:53
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"OPERATON_BASE_URL\": \"https://operaton-doc.open-regels.nl/engine-"
"rest\",\n"
"  \"OPERATON_CLIENT_ID\": \"operaton-mcp-client\",\n"
"  \"OPERATON_CLIENT_SECRET\": \"<secret-from-keycloak>\",\n"
"  \"OPERATON_TOKEN_URL\": \"https://acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl/realms/ronl/"
"protocol/openid-connect/token\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:62
msgid ""
"**Use for:** AI agents and MCP clients that need the full, unfiltered "
"Operaton surface without tenant scoping. The caller gets everything — all "
"process instances, all tasks, all deployments, all tenants — because there "
"is no organisation filter on this path."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:64
msgid ""
"**Not for:** Callers that need the RONL-specific abstractions (audit logging "
"through the RONL API, the curation gate, RONL-shaped response envelopes, "
"tenant-scoped access). Those callers should use Pattern 3."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:66
msgid ""
"**Important:** `operaton-mcp` does not know about the RONL Business API. "
"Pointing `OPERATON_BASE_URL` at `https://acc.api.open-regels.nl` is wrong — "
"the RONL Business API does not expose `engine-rest` paths. Routes like `/v1/"
"m2m/process-instance` do not exist; the M2M routes use a completely "
"different path structure (`/v1/m2m/process`, `/v1/m2m/task`, `/v1/m2m/"
"decision/:key`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:68
msgid "`operaton-doc` Docker setup"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:70
msgid ""
"The `operaton-doc` instance is dedicated to this use case. It is configured "
"with:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:72
msgid ""
"`CAMUNDA_BPM_AUTHORIZATION_ENABLED=false` — disables Operaton's built-in "
"resource-level authorization, which by default returns 404 (not 403) on "
"unauthorized resources and blocks `/process-instance`, `/history`, `/"
"deployment`, and other endpoints from external callers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:73
msgid ""
"`spring.security.oauth2.resourceserver.jwt.jwk-set-uri` pointing at the "
"Keycloak JWKS endpoint — enables Bearer token validation on `/engine-rest/"
"**`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:74
msgid ""
"A custom `operaton-security-config` JAR in `userlib` that scopes the JWT "
"`SecurityFilterChain` to `/engine-rest/**` only, leaving all other paths "
"(Cockpit, Tasklist) unprotected for browser access."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:76
msgid "The relevant files:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:77
msgid ""
"~/operaton/doc/\n"
"├── Dockerfile                      # Multi-stage: deps + security-config "
"JAR + operaton image\n"
"├── pom.xml                         # Pulls operaton-keycloak-jwt 1.1.0 + "
"spring-boot-starter-oauth2-resource-server\n"
"├── config/\n"
"│   └── default.yml                 # jwk-set-uri + JPA/Hibernate "
"autoconfigure exclusions\n"
"└── security-config/\n"
"    ├── pom.xml\n"
"    └── src/main/java/nl/openregels/operaton/security/\n"
"        └── OperatonSecurityConfig.java   # Two SecurityFilterChain beans: "
"Order(1) JWT for engine-rest, Order(2) permitAll for webapp"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:91
msgid "Pattern 3 — RONL Business API M2M routes (`/v1/m2m/*`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:93
msgid ""
"The RONL Business API exposes a curated subset of Operaton operations "
"through its own `/v1/m2m/*` route group. These routes are designed for "
"callers that need to interact with Operaton through the RONL layer — gaining "
"audit logging, the curation gate, and RONL-shaped response envelopes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:95
msgid "**Base URL:** `https://acc.api.open-regels.nl/v1/m2m`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:97
msgid ""
"**Authentication:** OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials via the `operaton-mcp-"
"client` Keycloak client. The token audience must be `ronl-business-api`. The "
"RONL Business API validates the token with `jwtMiddleware` — no "
"`tenantMiddleware` is applied, so no `municipality` claim is required."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:99
msgid ""
"**Path contract:** RONL-specific paths that do not mirror `engine-rest`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`engine-rest` path"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "M2M path"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /task`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /v1/m2m/task`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /task/{id}`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /v1/m2m/task/:id`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /process-instance`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /v1/m2m/process`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`POST /history/process-instance`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /v1/m2m/process/history`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`POST /decision-definition/key/:key/evaluate`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`POST /v1/m2m/decision/:key/evaluate`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /process-instance/:id/variables`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:101
msgid "`GET /v1/m2m/process/:id/variables`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:110
msgid ""
"There is no `/v1/m2m/process-instance`, `/v1/m2m/process-definition`, or `/"
"v1/m2m/history` — these `engine-rest` paths have no equivalent in the M2M "
"layer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:112
msgid ""
"The `M2M_ALLOWED_OPERATIONS` constant in `m2m.routes.ts` acts as a curation "
"gate — any operation not in the list returns `403 OPERATION_NOT_PERMITTED` "
"regardless of what Operaton supports. This is intentional: it gives platform "
"operators control over what M2M callers can do without changing "
"authentication or deployment configuration."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:114
msgid ""
"Requests through the M2M routes are written to the `audit_logs` PostgreSQL "
"table. Because the `operaton-mcp-client` token carries no `municipality` "
"claim, `tenant_id` is populated with the Keycloak `azp` claim (`operaton-mcp-"
"client`), making M2M activity queryable and distinguishable from human "
"caseworker activity."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:116
msgid ""
"**Use for:** Automation scripts, integration workflows, and future tooling "
"that should go through the RONL API layer for auditability, or that need the "
"RONL response envelope shape. Also appropriate for callers that should be "
"gated by the curation mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:118
msgid ""
"**Not for:** `operaton-mcp`. The MCP server constructs requests using native "
"`engine-rest` paths. Pointing it at the RONL Business API will result in 404 "
"on every tool call that uses process, deployment, or history endpoints, and "
"403 MISSING_TENANT on the standard caseworker routes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:120
msgid ""
"See [Operaton MCP Client]{1} for the full M2M route reference and "
"authentication setup."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:124
msgid "Why the patterns are incompatible"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:126
msgid ""
"The incompatibility is at the path level, not the authentication level. "
"`operaton-mcp` is a generated proxy over the Operaton OpenAPI spec — it "
"knows about `GET /task`, `POST /process-instance/suspended`, `GET /history/"
"variable-instance`, and so on. None of those paths exist under `/v1/m2m/`. "
"Conversely, a caller that knows about `/v1/m2m/process/:id/decision-"
"document` is speaking the RONL contract, not the Operaton contract, and has "
"no equivalent `engine-rest` path to call."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:128
msgid ""
"The `operaton-mcp-client` Keycloak client is shared across both Pattern 2 "
"and Pattern 3 — the same credentials work for both. But the "
"`OPERATON_BASE_URL` determines which pattern is in use:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "`OPERATON_BASE_URL`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "Pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "Works with `operaton-mcp`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "`https://operaton-doc.open-regels.nl/engine-rest`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "Pattern 2"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "`https://acc.api.open-regels.nl`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "Pattern 3"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:130
msgid "No — wrong path structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:137
msgid "Operaton authorization note"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:139
msgid ""
"By default, Operaton returns `404` (not `403`) on resources the caller lacks "
"`READ` permission for when its built-in authorization is enabled. This means "
"that on a default Operaton instance, endpoints like `/process-instance`, `/"
"process-definition`, `/history`, `/deployment`, `/job`, `/incident`, `/"
"user`, and `/group` will return 404 to any caller without explicit "
"authorization grants — including authenticated callers with a valid Bearer "
"token."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:141
msgid ""
"The correct solution for controlled environments (where access is governed "
"externally — by OIDC, by Caddy, or by the RONL Business API layer) is "
"`CAMUNDA_BPM_AUTHORIZATION_ENABLED=false`. This is set on `operaton-doc`. Do "
"not set it on production instances that serve multiple tenants through "
"Operaton's own authorization model."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:145
msgid "Decision guide"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:147
msgid "Use this to determine which pattern to use for a new integration:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-access-patterns.md:148
msgid ""
"Does the caller use the MCP protocol (operaton-mcp, Claude Desktop, GitHub "
"Copilot)?\n"
"  └─ Yes → Pattern 2. Point OPERATON_BASE_URL at engine-rest directly.\n"
"\n"
"Does the caller need audit logging through the RONL API?\n"
"  └─ Yes → Pattern 3. Use the /v1/m2m/* routes.\n"
"\n"
"Does the caller need operations not exposed by the M2M curation gate?\n"
"  └─ Yes → Pattern 2, or extend the M2M_ALLOWED_OPERATIONS list.\n"
"\n"
"Is the caller a human operator inspecting or managing processes?\n"
"  └─ Yes → Pattern 1. Use the Cockpit.\n"
"\n"
"Does the caller need tenant-scoped access (only data for one municipality)?\n"
"  └─ Yes → Use the standard caseworker routes (/v1/process, /v1/task, /v1/"
"decision)\n"
"            with a token that carries a municipality claim. Not a pattern "
"covered here."
msgstr ""
